# Testing rules

- For every new feature or behavior change, create or update unit tests automatically.
- Do not finish a code change unless relevant unit tests are added or updated.
- Use Vitest, jsdom, and React Testing Library for unit tests.
- Create a test file next to the component/utility: `MyComponent.test.tsx`.
- After modifying code, run `pnpm test` and fix any failing tests.
- Prefer small focused tests over broad integration-style tests.
- When changing UI text or interactions, update existing tests instead of deleting coverage.